  "summary": "Pulls typosquatted transitive dependency ruamel-yaml-clibz",
  "details": "The wheel METADATA declares a hard runtime dependency on `ruamel-yaml-clibz==0.3.5` (Requires-Dist line in nvidia_nat_semantic_kernel-1.8.0a20260607.dist-info/METADATA), a one-character variant of the legitimate `ruamel-yaml-clib` C-extension companion to ruamel.yaml. Any `pip install nvidia-nat-semantic-kernel` will resolve and install `ruamel-yaml-clibz` from PyPI, executing whatever code that unknown package ships on the installer's machine. Legitimate NVIDIA releases depend on `ruamel-yaml-clib`, not a one-letter variant — the substitution is consistent with dependency-confusion / typosquat injection smuggled into the install closure under cover of an NVIDIA-branded package.",
